cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.IR

This paper deals with facial expression recognition using image sequences, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses machine learning algorithms such as AdaBoost and support vector machines, which are commonly used in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with the tracking of facial landmarks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of facial expressions in social interactions, which is related to the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper uses dynamic time warping similarity distance, which is a common technique in the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
